<p>As a Principal, Dan serves as the primary point of client contact during our engagements.  
His responsibilities vary by project but typically include project management and both architectural 
and development leadership roles.  Dan has the ability to understand our client's business goals, create a list 
of project requirements, translate these requirements into the language of developers and lead the development effort.</p>
<p>Dan Goyette came to Nevo from Great Works Internet in 2009 joining as a developer on a project for Conservation Services Group where Nevo was building a residential energy efficiency assessment tool.</p>
<p>He grew into taking leadership roles in projects for several clients, including Cambridge Associates, Massey Quick, Ellevation, The Acushnet Company, and Bank of New York Mellon.
Dan takes ownership of tasks at all levels of the project, and effectively leads a team to successfully deliver on our clients' needs.</p>
<p>With a passion for computing and user experience design, Dan functions as a versatile and well-rounded member of any software development team.</p>
Dan holds a BA in Philosophy with a minor in Computer Science from University of Southern Maine.

